160
00:11:29.231 --> 00:11:32.234
I got caught up in my story
and you know how bad I wanted that.

161
00:11:33.277 --> 00:11:35.153
I never should have let it
come between us.

162
00:11:35.737 --> 00:11:37.823
Yeah. you shouldn't have.

163
00:11:38.699 --> 00:11:39.700
Close to forgiving me?

164
00:11:40.284 --> 00:11:41.576
I don't know. I'm circling it.

165
00:11:41.577 --> 00:11:43.286
Okay. come on. Let's go.

166
00:11:43.287 --> 00:11:44.997
Okay.

167
00:11:46.039 --> 00:11:47.582
You should put a Band-Aid on your head.

168
00:12:02.181 --> 00:12:04.892
Oh. shit. Fuck. fuck. fuck. fuck. fuck.

169
00:12:14.568 --> 00:12:16.320
I guess you missed the art show. huh?

170
00:12:17.321 --> 00:12:19.990
That's too bad.
It was like going to the Louvre.

171
00:12:20.574 --> 00:12:24.703
- But more Popsicle stick sculptures.
- Oh. Ah.

172
00:12:25.287 --> 00:12:28.164
Sorry that
I stood you up on our date.

173
00:12:28.165 --> 00:12:32.878
I am assuming you know the reason?

174
00:12:33.712 --> 00:12:34.795
Yeah.

175
00:12:34.796 --> 00:12:36.381
Never heard that one before.

176
00:12:36.924 --> 00:12:39.968
For what it's worth.
it's a huge mistake. you know.

177
00:12:40.928 --> 00:12:43.055
I've been presuming your innocence.

178
00:12:43.847 --> 00:12:45.681
Yeah. you always hear
you're supposed to do that.

179
00:12:45.682 --> 00:12:47.391
but I've never actually tried it before.

180
00:12:47.392 --> 00:12:48.684
Thank you for trying.

181
00:12:48.685 --> 00:12:52.689
It's. like. more than I can say
for anybody else. It's. like. so fucked.

182
00:12:54.024 --> 00:12:55.734
I c… I can't go to work.

183
00:12:56.944 --> 00:13:00.155
I can't go see
my own kid's art show. It's…

184
00:13:00.781 --> 00:13:01.823
Unlock your phone.

185
00:13:10.207 --> 00:13:11.749
There we go.

186
00:13:11.750 --> 00:13:16.212
So I just AirDropped you every
single masterpiece from the art show.

187
00:13:16.213 --> 00:13:17.505
Thank you.

188
00:13:17.506 --> 00:13:21.343
Look. there's even one of
Hazel's deeply nuanced watercolor of…

189
00:13:22.719 --> 00:13:24.053
Is that a parrot?

190
00:13:24.054 --> 00:13:26.097
Oh! I think that's Mallory.

191
00:13:26.098 --> 00:13:27.432
Oh! Y-Yeah.

192
00:13:28.225 --> 00:13:30.810
The same plumage.

193
00:13:32.104 --> 00:13:34.064
Thank you.

194
00:13:34.606 --> 00:13:35.691
Yeah.

195
00:13:36.191 --> 00:13:37.900
I gotta go.

196
00:13:37.901 --> 00:13:39.319
Okay. See you soon.

197
00:13:40.028 --> 00:13:42.447
Maybe like ten to 20. but wait for me.

198
00:13:59.840 --> 00:14:01.717
The bong attack is awesome.

199
00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:03.676
Wasn't. really.

200
00:14:03.677 --> 00:14:05.679
No. I mean for the article.
It's so cinematic.

201
00:14:07.222 --> 00:14:08.473
Wait. you're still writing that?

202
00:14:09.266 --> 00:14:11.518
Suzie's into it.
It could be my one shot at breaking in.

203
00:14:12.853 --> 00:14:13.854
One shot?

204
00:14:15.480 --> 00:14:17.398
Do you really think
you're not a good enough writer

205
00:14:17.399 --> 00:14:20.151
to come up with. like.
other. better stories

206
00:14:20.152 --> 00:14:21.527
that don't hurt your friends?

207
00:14:21.528 --> 00:14:23.155
I honestly don't know.

208
00:14:24.865 --> 00:14:25.991
Okay. well. I do.

209
00:14:27.451 --> 00:14:29.411
I-I have no doubt.

210
00:14:32.122 --> 00:14:37.169
'Cause underneath that snark.
you are a really good person.

211
00:14:39.505 --> 00:14:41.840
You will hate yourself if you do this.

212
00:14:47.346 --> 00:14:48.847
That was shockingly kind.

213
00:14:49.681 --> 00:14:50.682
Fine.

214
00:14:51.308 --> 00:14:52.309
No article.

215
00:14:53.143 --> 00:14:54.435
Yeah?

216
00:14:54.436 --> 00:14:55.437
Shit.

217
00:14:55.938 --> 00:14:57.647
You could make a really good lawyer.

218
00:14:57.648 --> 00:14:59.607
Although you'll probably fail the LSATs.

219
00:14:59.608 --> 00:15:01.777
Well. Ger-Bear.

220
00:15:02.736 --> 00:15:04.111
you back.

221
00:15:04.112 --> 00:15:05.196
Come here.

222
00:15:05.197 --> 00:15:06.823
- Thank you.
- I know.

223
00:15:18.126 --> 00:15:19.627
Is Paula's around here?

224
00:15:19.628 --> 00:15:21.088
Yeah. I think it's… little more this way.

225
00:15:26.134 --> 00:15:27.260
Uh. f…

226
00:15:27.261 --> 00:15:28.636
Hey.

227
00:15:28.637 --> 00:15:30.346
<i>Hey. Paula.
I don't want to alarm you.</i>

228
00:15:30.347 --> 00:15:31.472
<i>but time is ticking.</i>

229
00:15:31.473 --> 00:15:35.768
We were just assigned a custody
hearing date. and it is next week.

230
00:15:35.769 --> 00:15:38.312
Uh. next week?
What-What are you talking about?

231
00:15:38.313 --> 00:15:39.397
I'm out on bail.

232
00:15:39.398 --> 00:15:41.649
That's what I argued.
but Judge Narleski ruled

233
00:15:41.650 --> 00:15:43.693
